# 8. ほほ笑み

Miku: Oh... Kanade, they're here...
Kanade: I know you're both busy and were just about to get started, but thanks for meeting me here.
Mizuki: Nah, it's all good! I just sat down a second ago so it's not like I was really doing anything.
Ena: Same here. And Mafuyu said she'll be running late, right...?
Kanade: Yes. She said she has to get ready for cram school.
Rin: So what are we doing? Listening to another song?
Kanade: Yes. There's something I'd like you to listen to. Would that be alright, Rin?
Rin: Fine.
Mizuki: You feel pretty good about it...?
Kanade: I do.
Kanade: I'm not sure if it'll strike a chord with Mafuyu but... Oh...
Kanade: Mafuyu...
Mafuyu: Is it true that you made a new demo...?
Kanade: Yes. More than that, it's basically a full song.
Kanade: Would you like to listen to it...?
Mafuyu: Yes, that's why I'm here.
Ena: You could say that a little nicer, you know? She went through the trouble of making this for you...
Mafuyu: I didn't mean to be rude.
Ena: I'm saying the way you naturally talk is rude!
Mafuyu: I see.
Ena: Ugh... You...!
Mizuki: Okay, okay! Relax! Let's just settle down and listen to Kanade's song!
Kanade: Right, here it goes.
Kanade: (How's Mafuyu reacting...?)
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: (This one didn't work either...)
Mafuyu: It finished...
Ena: Yeah, we know, we listened to it too. Don't you have anything else to say?
Mafuyu: Anything else...?
Mafuyu: I'm not sure how to describe it...
Mafuyu: But I liked it, I think...
Kanade: Huh...?
Mizuki: Mafuyu smiled...?!
Mafuyu: ...?
Mafuyu: Why do you all look so surprised?
Ena: Wait, you have no idea what you just did?
Mizuki: You smiled, Mafuyu! It's because of Kanade's song!
Mafuyu: I am...?
Ena: What made you smile? Was it the chorus?
Mafuyu: I don't know... I don't know but...
Mafuyu: It felt... Warm...
Kanade: Mafuyu...
Luka: Now I understand.
Kanade: What?
Luka: That is what you all want to feel.
Kanade: I see...
Kanade: I finally get it, dad.
Mafuyu: <I'm logging off now.>
Ena: <Me too. Good night, you two.>
Mizuki: <See ya! Night, Yuki, Enanan!>
Mizuki: <Whoa, it's pretty late. I'm gonna head off in a bit too.>
Kanade: <Okay.>
Kanade: <Thanks again, Amia...>
Kanade: <I was able to compose that song because you helped me open my eyes.>
Mizuki: <I opened your eyes...? Haha. You're exaggerating way too much, K.>
Mizuki: <But that's good...>
Mizuki: <I'm glad that I was able to help.>
Mizuki: (I opened her eyes, huh...?)
Mizuki: (For the longest time, I had such a cynical view of the world and just assumed that none of it mattered...)
Mizuki: (But if Kanade's saying that I was actually able to help her, I guess the things I've done up to this point weren't a complete waste.)
Mizuki: (She's such an incredible human being too...)
Mizuki: (Not only does she have to take care of her dad, she keeps making all these songs even though she's dealing with so many other things.)
Mizuki: (She works tirelessly to try and save people.)
Mizuki: Giving up has probably never crossed her mind...
Mizuki: Will I be able to change if I do that too?
Mizuki: But still... Kanade's really something else.
Mizuki: She's the reason the old me and the current me have been able to keep going.
Mizuki: Alright, I need to try a little harder too. I don't have a big goal or anything yet...
Mizuki: But I can start by making a music video that fits this song perfectly!
